{"cursor":"58175","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n{{Multiple issues|\n\n\n\n\n\n}} {{Infobox anatomy\n| Name = Hair Latin = GraySubject = GrayPage = Image = Gray945.png Caption =\n| Cross section of a hair Image2 = Caption2 = Map = MapPos = MapCaption =\n| Precursor = System = Artery = Vein = Nerve = Lymph = MeshName = MeshNumber =\n| Code = TH H3.12.00.3.02001\n}} 'Hair' is a filamentous biomaterial that grows from follicles found in the\ndermis. Hair is one of the defining characteristics of mammals.\n\nThe human body, apart from areas of glabrous skin, is covered in follicles which\nproduce thick terminal and fine vellus hair. Most common interest in hair is\nfocused on hair growth, hair types and hair care, but hair is also an important\nbiomaterial primarily composed of protein, notably keratin. In many human\nsocieties, women predominantly grow the hair on their head long while men cut\ntheirs short.\n","linknr":1129,"url":"Hair","recorded":1362373460,"links":160,"instances":["biology","the_walking_dead","hair_removal","contemporary_subculture","hair","hair","psychology","film","stereotype","the_walking_dead","musical","hair","zoology"],"pdf":["http://jap.physiology.org/cgi/reprint/36/2/256.pdf","http://jap.physiology.org/cgi/reprint/36/2/256.pdf","http://icb.oxfordjournals.org/content/40/4/585.full.pdf","http://icb.oxfordjournals.org/content/40/4/585.full.pdf","http://users.utu.fi/mjranta/reprints/1.%20Rantala1999.pdf","http://users.utu.fi/mjranta/reprints/1.%20Rantala1999.pdf","http://hmg.oxfordjournals.org/content/17/6/835.full.pdf","http://hmg.oxfordjournals.org/content/17/6/835.full.pdf","http://www.tulips.tsukuba.ac.jp/dspace/bitstream/2241/103672/1/HG_124-2.pdf","http://www.tulips.tsukuba.ac.jp/dspace/bitstream/2241/103672/1/HG_124-2.pdf"],"categories":["Articles with inconsistent citation formats","Human hair|"],"headings":["Overview","Description","Function","Evolution","Removal practices","Social role","In popular culture","S